# Local dev defaults. For Play Store / release APK+AAB builds, copy `.env.production.example`
# → `.env.production` (gitignored) and run `npm run build:mobile:prod` — that picks up
# VITE_TARGET=capacitor and prod Supabase URL/key.
#
# Supabase – MUST be same as main ERP (web) so one database, same login.
# Copy these from project root .env.production or .env.local (same VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY as web).
# Production: https://supabase.dincouture.pk + Kong anon key from VPS.
#
# Do NOT use the public Supabase tutorial anon JWT (iss "supabase-demo") — Realtime warns and you may hit
# the wrong project; Pay Supplier (record_payment_with_accounting) and SQL migrations only apply to YOUR DB.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL + VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY must match that project (copy from web .env.production).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL must stay the real HTTPS API URL (not localhost) even in dev: the app uses it for
# direct wss:// Realtime while REST/auth go through Vite same-origin proxy.
#
# Optional: VITE_DISABLE_REALTIME=true — turn off postgres_changes (e.g. if Kong blocks wss from localhost).
# Optional: VITE_SUPABASE_PROXY_ORIGIN=https://erp.dincouture.pk — outbound Origin for Vite→Kong proxy (see vite.config.ts).
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://supabase.dincouture.pk
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-from-web-app

# Pay Supplier RPC fixes (same Postgres as web): paste migrations/rollups/record_payment_allocation_fix_bundle.sql in Supabase SQL Editor once if Pay refs fail.
